'''Okinawa Prefectural Onoyama Park''' (沖縄県営奥武山公園, '''Okinawa Ken'ei Ounoyama Kōen''') is a {{ill|Sports park|ja|運動公園|12=draft}} located in {{ill|Naha|ja|那覇市|12=draft}}, {{ill|Okinawa Prefecture|ja|沖縄県|12=draft}}.
== Overview ==
Established in {{ill|June 1959|ja|1959th year 6月|12=draft}} as Okinawa Prefecture's first sports park, it serves as the main venue for the annual {{ill|Naha Festival|ja|那覇まつり|12=draft}} and the {{ill|Okinawa Industrial Festival|ja|沖縄の産業まつり|12=draft}} held every October.
* '''Management Office:''' Onoyama Comprehensive Sports Park Management Office (located within the Martial Arts Hall) * '''Address:''' 52 Onoyama-cho, Naha, Okinawa Prefecture * '''Classification:''' Sports park * '''Area:''' 24.99 ha<ref>[http://www3.pref.okinawa.jp/site/view/contview.jsp?cateid=213&id=13974&page=1 Okinawa Prefecture Civil Engineering and Construction Department Onoyama Park]</ref> * '''Facilities:''' {{ill|Athletics stadium|ja|陸上競技場|12=draft}}, {{ill|Baseball field|ja|野球場|12=draft}}, {{ill|Tennis courts|ja|テニスコート|12=draft}}, {{ill|Martial arts hall|ja|武道館|12=draft}}<ref>The Okinawa Prefectural Onoyama Gymnasium, which existed before the construction of the Martial Arts Hall, was demolished to make way for the current facility.</ref>, {{ill|Archery range|ja|弓道場|12=draft}}, {{ill|Swimming pool|ja|プール|12=draft}}, among others. * '''Designated Manager:''' Trust Tech Co., Ltd.<ref>[http://www3.pref.okinawa.lg.jp/site/contents/attach/19486/list.pdf Facilities Implementing the Designated Manager System in Okinawa Prefecture (PDF)]</ref> (Headquarters: 303 Orokku, Naha, Okinawa Prefecture)
== Usage Fees ==
Fees vary depending on the time slot but generally average around ¥8,000 for the athletics stadium, under ¥5,000 for the baseball field, and about ¥2,000 for the swimming pool. These are usage fees when no general admission fees are charged. See the official site for more details.
== Facilities ==
=== Athletics Stadium === [[File:NAHA Marathon02n.jpg|thumb|250px|Athletics Stadium ({{ill|Naha Marathon|ja|NAHAマラソン|12=draft}})]] Opened on August 31, 1970, it hosts events such as the {{ill|Naha Marathon|ja|NAHAマラソン|12=draft}}, Okinawa Prefectural Ground Golf Tournament, {{ill|Naha Festival|ja|那覇まつり|12=draft}}, and the 1997 {{ill|10 Million People Radio Exercise Festival|ja|1000万人ラジオ体操・みんなの体操祭|12=draft}}.
* '''Capacity:''' A11roximately 9,000 (turf stands) * '''Certification:''' Not certified by the Japan Association of Athletics Federations * '''Track:''' 400m, 8 lanes * '''Additional Facilities:''' Auxiliary track (dirt)
==== Soccer Field Construction Plans ====
In February 2013, Naha City announced plans to rebuild the athletics stadium as a soccer-specific stadium meeting {{ill|J-League Club Licensing Standards|ja|Jリーグクラブライセンス制度|12=draft}}. The plan projected a capacity of 20,000, a total cost of approximately ¥13 billion, construction starting in fiscal 2016, and completion by fiscal 2019.
